how can i get reffered to a dermatologist here in the uk if you are registered with a general practioner first visit him with your symptoms if his prescribed treatment does not work then ask him to reffer you to a dermathologist for a second opinion and to have tests done to confirm diagnosis you may have to wait for quite a while to get an appointment otherwise you can also ask for a letter and consult an approved private consultant but be prepared to pay for his fees hope this information is of some help to you good luck Diagnosis Prostate cancer Dermatology Medicine Malignant melanoma Eczema Psychiatry Paget's disease of bone Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Stomach cancer Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders Gastroesophageal reflux disease Lupus erythematosus Fibromyalgia Pharmaceutical company Lymphogranuloma venereum Malaria Coeliac disease Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome Growth hormone treatment Traditional Chinese medicine Homeopathy Rosacea Legal aspects of transsexualism Clinical depression Publicly funded medicine Alternative medicine Syphilis Antidepressant Migraine Transsexuality Cancer Medical record Psoriasis Anxiety Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Epilepsy Legionellosis Rheumatoid arthritis Restless legs syndrome Internal medicine Gonorrhoea Cystic fibrosis Dentistry Group A streptococcal infection Chronic lymphocytic leukemia Pneumonia Kaposi's sarcoma Gout Constitution of Fiji: Chapter 11 Asthma Narcolepsy Conjunctivitis Allergy Traumatic brain injury Botulin toxin Sleep apnea Terri Schiavo Lung cancer Breast cancer Prolactinoma Prenatal diagnosis Endometriosis Amineptine Beh__et's disease Public domain M__ni__re___s disease Huntington's disease Buprenorphine Mental Health Act 1983 Chronic fatigue syndrome London Congestion Charge President of Ireland Nurse Antipsychotic Adolf Hitler's medical health Pelvic inflammatory disease Hypoglycemia Avian influenza Pulmonary embolism 